    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-30T12:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-30T12:29:00-05:00" n="364"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.51/306</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scholle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-30T12:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1918, 12 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 29, 1 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d364fn1">Not printed.</note> I called
                    personally on Secretary of the Treasury on receipt of your April 20, 6 p.m., and
                    urged him to get me the information at once. He promised to attend to the matter
                    himself. Since then I have daily, through the Subsecretary of State, urged
                    haste. Am again to-day insisting on question being answered immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scholle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
